{
  "_comment": [
    "CoMD molecular-dynamics benchmark \u2014 4 MPI ranks throughout.",
    "",
    "Active scenarios for the first benchmark cycle: small load \u00d7 {nofail, low}.",
    "  small load        \u2248 120s error-free at 4 ranks",
    "  low frequency     = 1 failure injected per run, mid-execution",
    "",
    "The full 3 (load) \u00d7 3 (frequency) + 3 (nofail) matrix is documented in",
    "_TODO_full_matrix below; promote entries into the active 'scenarios' list",
    "once the small-low scenario is validated end-to-end on this hardware.",
    "",
    "Scenario naming: <load>-<frequency>",
    "Frequency mapping (Interpretation C \u2014 failures inside ONE run):",
    "  nofail \u2192 failures_per_run=0, inject_failures=false, max_attempts=1",
    "  low    \u2192 failures_per_run=1, injection_delay = T_golden / 2",
    "  mid    \u2192 failures_per_run=3, injection_delay = T_golden / 4",
    "  high   \u2192 failures_per_run=6, injection_delay = T_golden / 7",
    "  max_attempts = failures_per_run + 2 (room for the final clean attempt)."
  ],
  "scenarios": [
    {
      "name": "small-nofail",
      "_purpose": "Golden: error-free baseline timing (~206s at 4 ranks). NB: -N (capital) = nSteps, -n (lowercase) = printRate. With -N 1500 -n 100 the simulation loop iterates 15 times at iStep \u2208 {0,100,...,1400}, allowing CoMD's checkpoint cadence (every 500 steps) to actually fire at iStep=500 and iStep=1000.",
      "num_procs": 4,
      "app_args": [
        "-x",
        "80",
        "-y",
        "80",
        "-z",
        "20",
        "-N",
        "1500",
        "-n",
        "100",
        "-i",
        "2",
        "-j",
        "2",
        "-k",
        "1"
      ],
      "inject_failures": false,
      "num_runs": 3,
      "injection_delay": 0.0,
      "max_attempts": 1,
      "failures_per_run": 0
    },
    {
      "name": "small-low",
      "_purpose": "1 failure injected at 100s \u2014 after the iStep=500 checkpoint fires (~67s in) but before iStep=1000 (~134s), so the restart loads a real checkpoint and only redoes ~1000 of the 1500 steps.",
      "num_procs": 4,
      "app_args": [
        "-x",
        "80",
        "-y",
        "80",
        "-z",
        "20",
        "-N",
        "1500",
        "-n",
        "100",
        "-i",
        "2",
        "-j",
        "2",
        "-k",
        "1"
      ],
      "inject_failures": true,
      "num_runs": 3,
      "injection_delay": 74.2,
      "max_attempts": 3,
      "failures_per_run": 1
    }
  ],
